    "body" : "<p>While the accepted answer by afraisse is absolutely correct in terms of using <code>@RequestParam</code>, I would further suggest to use an Optional&lt;> as you cannot always ensure the right parameter is used. Also, if you need an Integer or Long just use that data type to avoid casting types later on in the DAO.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@RequestMapping(value=\"/data\", method = RequestMethod.GET)\npublic @ResponseBody\nItem getItem(@RequestParam(\"itemid\") Optional&lt;Integer&gt; itemid) { \n    if( itemid.isPresent()){\n         Item i = itemDao.findOne(itemid.get());              \n         return i;\n     } else ....\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
